nch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the deluge that forced the postponement of the men's event the previous day, the sun returned Sunday and the temporary arena became a humid cauldron.\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Skaters can afford to fall and not register a score up to four times in their seven attempts.\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yoshizawa went into her penultimate trick with two big scores but needing a third to complete her total.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She still went for a high-risk ride down the handrail, and nailed it.\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though all her rivals had one more run, she raised her board above her head in triumph.\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The skateboarding resumes on Monday with the men's street event postponed from Saturday.\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1320, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With defending Olympic champion Yuto Horigome, Sora Shirai and 14-year-old Ginwoo Onodera, Japan could again dominate.\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1354, \"end\": 1367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuto_Horigome_(skateboarder)\", \"score\": 0.9999999629922065, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yuto Horigome\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuto_Horigome_(skateboarder)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yuto_Horigome_(skateboarder)\"}, {\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Kingdom_Hearts\", \"score\": 0.9745150567263647, \"rank\": 0.026124154057530113, \"text\": \"Sora\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_